events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Derrick Henry rushed for 147 yards with three touchdowns and No. 3 Alabama ran away with a 35-17 victory over No. 20 Wisconsin in the season opener for both teams Saturday night.

video.headline: Alabama rolls behind Henry's big night

headlines.shortLinkText: Henry, No. 3 Bama rumble by No. 20 Wisconsin

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Will Muschamp's defense made a couple of huge plays early for No. 6 Auburn to offset three interceptions by Jeremy Johnson, and the Tigers held off Louisville and surprise quarterback Lamar Jacks
headlines.shortLinkText: Muschamp defense helps No. 6 Auburn beat Louisville 31-24

events.name: Eastern Washington Eagles at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Vernon Adams threw for two touchdowns but left his much-anticipated debut after a scary fourth-quarter hit, and No. 7 Oregon defeated his former team, Eastern Washington, 61-42 to open the season

video.headline: Adams impressive for Ducks against former team

headlines.shortLinkText: Adams makes debut in 61-42 Oregon win over E. Washington

events.name: Arkansas State Red Wolves at USC Trojans

headlines.description: Cody Kessler passed for 236 yards and four touchdowns, Tre Madden rushed for 106 yards and a score, and No. 8 Southern California beat Arkansas State 55-6 Saturday night in its season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kessler's 4 TD passes lead No. 8 USC past Arkansas St, 55-6

events.name: Louisiana Monroe Warhawks at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: With lightning in the area, No. 9 Georgia defeated Louisiana-Monroe 51-14 on Saturday in a one-sided game that was called off with just under 10 minutes left.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 9 Georgia tops Louisiana-Monroe 51-14; game called early

events.name: Texas State Bobcats at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Everett Golson threw four touchdown passes in his Florida State debut to help the 10th-ranked Seminoles beat Texas State 59-16 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Golson throws 4 TD passes in debut for No. 10 Florida State

events.name: Texas Longhorns at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Malik Zaire passed for 313 yards in his first home start, and No. 11 Notre Dame held Texas to 163 yards of total offense in a 38-3 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zaire throws for 313 yards, Notre Dame beats Texas 38-3

events.name: Wofford Terriers at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Deshaun Watson threw for 194 yards and two touchdowns in less than a half and Clemson moved to 30-0 against FCS opponents with a 49-10 victory over Wofford on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Watson throws for 2 TDs, No. 12 Clemson routs Wofford 49-10

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Heralded freshman Josh Rosen passed for 351 yards and three touchdowns in a stellar debut for UCLA, leading the No. 13 Bruins to a 34-16 victory over Virginia on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rosen leads No. 13 UCLA past Virginia 34-16 in stellar debut

events.name: Arizona State Sun Devils at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Kyle Allen threw for a score early and sealed the game by running for a touchdown and throwing for another in the fourth quarter after being benched in favor of freshman Kyler Murray, and Texas A

video.headline: Christian Kirk's big day powers Texas A&M

headlines.shortLinkText: Allen leads Texas A&M over No. 15 Arizona State 38-17

events.name: Tennessee-Martin Skyhawks at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Chad Kelly threw for 211 yards and two touchdowns and also ran for a 20-yard touchdown to lead No. 17 Mississippi past UT Martin 76-3 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 17 Mississippi dominant in 76-3 win over UT Martin

events.name: UTEP Miners at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Brandon Allen threw for a career-high 308 yards and matched his best with four touchdown passes as No. 18 Arkansas opened its season with a 48-13 win over UTEP on Saturday.

video.headline: Arkansas makes easy work of UTEP

headlines.shortLinkText: Allen's career day leads No. 18 Arkansas past UTEP 48-13

events.name: Akron Zips at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Baker Mayfield passed for 388 yards and three touchdowns, and Joe Mixon had 142 yards from scrimmage to help No. 19 Oklahoma defeat Akron 41-3 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mayfield leads No. 19 Oklahoma past Akron 41-3

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Freshman Clayton Thorson ran 42 yards for a touchdown while playing turnover-free ball at quarterback, Justin Jackson added 134 yards rushing, and Northwestern beat No. 21 Stanford 16-6.
headlines.shortLinkText: Error-free Northwestern upends No. 21 Stanford

events.name: Southeast Missouri State Redhawks at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Kentrell Brothers had a career-best 16 tackles and blocked a punt that was returned for a touchdown for No. 24 Missouri, which opened with a 34-3 victory over Southeast Missouri State on Saturday
headlines.shortLinkText: Brothers leads No. 24 Missouri past Southeast Missouri 34-3

events.name: Bowling Green Falcons at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Jalen Hurd had three first-half touchdown runs, Alvin Kamara ran for two more scores, and No. 25 Tennessee beat Bowling Green 59-30 on Saturday in a season opener delayed 80 minutes by lightning.

video.headline: Vols run all over Bowling Green

headlines.shortLinkText: No. 25 Tennessee runs for 6 TDs, beats Bowling Green 59-30

events.name: South Dakota State Jackrabbits at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description: Zach Lujan threw for 293 yards and three touchdowns, Isaac Wallace ran for 118 yards and another score and South Dakota State spoiled the debut of Kansas coach David Beaty with a 41-38 victory ov
headlines.shortLinkText: South Dakota State holds on to knock off Kansas, 41-38

events.name: Illinois State Redbirds at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: C.J. Beathard threw for 211 yards and a touchdown in his first career start at Kinnick Stadium and Iowa pounded Illinois State 31-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa pounds Illinois State 31-14

events.name: Richmond Spiders at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: William Likely set a Big Ten record with 233 yards in punt returns, Brandon Ross ran for career-high 150 yards and one touchdown as Maryland rolled to a season-opening 50-21 victory over Richmond
headlines.shortLinkText: Maryland scored 37 straight points and beats Richmond 50-21

events.name: Norfolk State Spartans at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Leonte Carroo caught three third-quarter touchdown passes after sitting out a first-half suspension and set a school record as Rutgers overcame the distractions of an academic investigation invol
headlines.shortLinkText: Carroo catches 3 TDs as Rutgers overcomes distractions

events.name: Colgate Raiders at Navy Midshipmen

headlines.description: Chris Swain rumbled for 126 yards, including a 52-yard touchdown, all in the first half and Navy cruised over Colgate 48-10 in the opener for both teams Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Navy runs past Colgate 48-10

events.name: Maine Black Bears at Boston College Eagles

headlines.description: Tyler Rouse rushed for 81 yards scored a pair of fourth quarter touchdowns, allowing Boston College to pull away from Maine 24-3 in the season opener for both teams Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boston College beats Maine, 24-3

events.name: Youngstown State Penguins at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: Redshirt freshman Qadree Ollison ran for 207 yards while filling in for injured star James Conner and Pittsburgh survived Youngstown State 45-37 on Saturday to give Pat Narduzzi a victory in his
headlines.shortLinkText: Pitt survives Youngstown State 45-37 in opener

events.name: Portland State Vikings at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Steven Long scored on a 1-yard run with just over 2 minutes left in the game to lift Portland State to a 24-17 upset of Washington State Saturday in a steady rain storm that hampered the Cougars'
headlines.shortLinkText: Portland State upsets Washington State 24-17

events.name: Kent State Golden Flashes at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: Wes Lunt passed for four touchdowns and Illinois routed Kent State 52-3 in the opener for both teams on Saturday, a day after it was re-scheduled due to lightning.
headlines.shortLinkText: Illinois scores cathartic win over Kent State 52-3

events.name: Sam Houston State Bearkats at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Patrick Mahomes threw for 425 yards and four touchdowns, two each to Ian Sadler and Devin Lauderdale, to lead Texas Tech past Sam Houston State 59-45 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas Tech upends Sam Houston St. 59-45 in season opener

events.name: BYU Cougars at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Mitch Mathews caught backup quarterback Tanner Mangum's 42-yard Hail Mary with no time left, giving BYU a 33-28 victory over Nebraska and spoiling the debut of new Cornhuskers coach Mike Riley.

video.headline: BYU stuns Nebraska on final-play Hail Mary

headlines.shortLinkText: BYU Hail Mary stuns Nebraska, ends win streak

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Temple Owls

headlines.description: P.J. Walker scored the go-ahead touchdown late in the third quarter to rally Temple to a 27-10 win over Penn State on Saturday. It was the Owls' first win over the Nittany Lions in 74 years.

video.headline: Temple shuts down Hackenberg, Penn State

headlines.shortLinkText: Temple defeats Penn State for first time since '41

events.name: Old Dominion Monarchs at Eastern Michigan Eagles

headlines.description: Ray Lawry ran for 223 yards and four touchdowns to lead Old Dominion to a 38-34 come-from-behind win over Eastern Michigan in the season opener for both teams Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Old Dominion overtakes Eastern Michigan 38-34

events.name: Florida Atlantic Owls at Tulsa Golden Hurricane

headlines.description: Zack Langer rushed for three touchdowns, including the winner in overtime, to help Tulsa slip past FAU 47-44 in the season opener for both teams on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lucas, Langer help Tulsa rally past FAU, 47-44, in overtime

events.name: Morgan State Bears at Air Force Falcons

headlines.description: Nate Romine threw for 119 yards and two touchdowns and D.J. Johnson added 82 yards and a touchdown on the ground to help lead Air Force to a 63-7 win over Morgan State in the season opening game
headlines.shortLinkText: Air Force runs over Morgan State, 63-7

events.name: Albany Great Danes at Buffalo Bulls

headlines.description: Joe Licata threw two touchdowns to lead Buffalo to a 51-14 win over Albany (N.Y.) on Saturday in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Buffalo defeats Albany (NY) 51-14

events.name: Presbyterian College Blue Hose at Miami (OH) RedHawks

headlines.description: Drew Kummer threw two touchdown passes, Alonzo Smith ran for two, and Miami (Ohio) beat Presbyterian 26-7 in the opener for both teams on Saturday in a game interrupted in the third quarter due t
headlines.shortLinkText: Kummer helps Miami (Ohio) over Presbyterian 26-7

events.name: Howard Bison at Appalachian State Mountaineers

headlines.description: Taylor Lamb completed 17 of 22 passes for 226 yards and four touchdowns to lead Appalachian State to a 49-0 win over Howard in a season opener on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lamb leads Appalachian State over Howard 49-0

events.name: Southern Illinois Salukis at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: Jordan Howard rushed for 145 yards and three touchdowns to help Indiana slip past Southern Illinois 48-47 in the season opener for both teams on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Howard's 3 TDs, late stop lift Indiana over S. Illinois

events.name: Savannah State Tigers at Colorado State Rams

headlines.description: Nick Stevens threw for 289 yards and five touchdowns in his first career start, and Colorado State rolled past Savannah State 65-13 on Saturday to give Mike Bobo a victory in his head coaching de
headlines.shortLinkText: Stevens has 5 TDs, Colorado St. dominates Savannah St. 65-13

events.name: North Dakota Fighting Hawks at Wyoming Cowboys

venue.fullName: Jonah Field at War Memorial Stadium

headlines.description: John Santiago ran for 148 yards and two touchdowns to lead North Dakota to a 24-13 victory over Wyoming in the season opener for both teams on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Santiago with 2 touchdowns; North Dakota beats Wyoming 24-13

events.name: Wagner Seahawks at Rice Owls

headlines.description: Darik Dillard ran for two touchdowns and Rice rolled over Wagner 56-16 in the opener for both teams on Saturday in a game that was delayed at the start by foul weather.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rice rolls over Wagner 56-16

events.name: Grambling State Tigers at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Jared Goff threw for 309 yards and three touchdowns in one half and California returned two interceptions for scores to beat Grambling State 73-14 in a season opener Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Goff throws 3 TDs in 1st half as Cal beats Grambling 73-14

events.name: Bethune-Cookman Wildcats at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Brad Kaaya passed for 173 yards and two touchdowns, Corn Elder ran a punt 72 yards for a score and Miami beat Bethune-Cookman 45-0 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knighton makes debut, Miami rolls past Bethune 45-0

events.name: Troy Trojans at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description: Matt Dayes ran for a career-high 126 yards and two touchdowns while Jaylen Samuels ran for three scores of his own to help North Carolina State beat Troy 49-21 on Saturday night in the opener for
headlines.shortLinkText: Dayes, Samuels help NC State roll past Troy 49-21 in opener

events.name: Towson Tigers at East Carolina Pirates

headlines.description: Chris Hairston rushed for 154 yards and four touchdowns, both career highs, to help East Carolina beat Towson 28-20 in the season opener for both teams on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hairston's 4 TDs lead East Carolina past Towson, 28-20

events.name: Gardner-Webb Bulldogs at South Alabama Jaguars

headlines.description: Xavier Johnson rushed for 121 yards and South Alabama beat Gardner-Webb 33-22 in the opener for both teams Saturday in a game delayed in the first half by heavy rains.
headlines.shortLinkText: South Alabama uses big plays to beat Gardner-Webb 33-22

events.name: Morehead State Eagles at James Madison Dukes

headlines.description: Vad Lee threw three touchdowns and ran for another as James Madison rolled over Morehead State 56-7 in a season opener on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: James Madison beats Morehead State 56-7

events.name: Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Mikel Horton's 12-yard run with 57 seconds remaining helped Kentucky overcome blowing a three-touchdown lead and escape Louisiana-Lafayette 40-33 Saturday night in the season opener for both squa
headlines.shortLinkText: Horton's TD helps Kentucky escape Louisiana-Lafayette 40-33

events.name: Southern Jaguars at Louisiana Tech Bulldogs

headlines.description: Jeff Driskel threw four touchdown passes and ran for another to lead Louisiana Tech over Southern 62-15 in the season opener for each team Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Driskel totals 5 TDs, Louisiana Tech tops Southern 62-15

events.name: Jackson State Tigers at Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders

headlines.description: Brent Stockstill threw four touchdowns to help Middle Tennessee to a 70-14 win over Jackson State in a season opener on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Middle Tennessee beats Jackson State 70-14

events.name: Missouri State Bears at Memphis Tigers

headlines.description: Doroland Dorceus and Jarvis Cooper ran for two touchdowns apiece, Mose Frazier caught two scoring passes and Memphis beat Missouri State 63-7 in Saturday's season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Memphis downs Missouri State 63-7 in opener

events.name: Florida A&M Rattlers at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: Quinton Flowers threw for two touchdowns and ran for another in his second career start to lead South Florida to a 51-3 victory over Florida A&M.
headlines.shortLinkText: South Florida gets rolling to beat Florida A&M 51-3

events.name: Coastal Carolina Chanticleers at Furman Paladins

headlines.description: Alex Ross threw for 328 yards and two touchdowns, both to Bruce Mapp, to help lead Coastal Carolina to a 38-35 win over Furman in the season opener for both teams on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coastal Carolina sneaks past Furman, 38-35

events.name: Delaware State Hornets at Liberty Flames

headlines.description: Josh Woodrum connected with Darrin Peterson on a pair of touchdowns as Liberty defeated Delaware State 32-13 in a season opener for both teams on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Liberty defeats Delaware State in season opener, 32-13

events.name: South Dakota Coyotes at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: Winston Dimel punched in two touchdowns Saturday and helped lead Kansas State to a 34-0 win over South Dakota in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kansas State rolls past South Dakota 34-0

events.name: New Mexico State Aggies at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Will Grier accounted for three touchdowns, Treon Harris threw for two more and Florida opened the Jim McElwain era by overwhelming New Mexico State 61-13 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida opens McElwain era with 61-13 rout of New Mexico St

events.name: Georgia Southern Eagles at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Skyler Howard threw two touchdown passes in his first home start, Karl Joseph had three interceptions and West Virginia beat Georgia Southern 44-0 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: West Virginia beats Georgia Southern 44-0

events.name: UNLV Rebels at Northern Illinois Huskies

headlines.description: Joel Bouagnon ran for three second-half touchdowns and Northern Illinois rallied from a 17-3 first-half deficit to beat UNLV 38-30 in the season opener on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bouagnon leads Northern Illinois comeback over UNLV, 38-30

events.name: Northern Iowa Panthers at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: Sam Richardson threw two touchdown passes and Iowa State got rolling in the second half to open the season with a 31-7 victory over Northern Iowa on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa State turns back Northern Iowa 31-7 before record crowd

events.name: Tennessee Tech Golden Eagles at Houston Cougars

headlines.description: Greg Ward Jr. threw for one touchdown and ran for two more and Houston rolled over Tennessee Tech, 52-24 in the season opener for both schools on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ward's 3 TDs spark Houston in  52-24 win over Tennessee Tech

events.name: San Diego Toreros at San Diego State Aztecs

headlines.description: Calvin Munson returned two interceptions for touchdowns to lead San Diego State to a 37-3 victory over San Diego in the season opener for both teams on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: San Diego State with 5 interceptions, beats San Diego 37-3

events.name: Mississippi Valley State Delta Devils at New Mexico Lobos

headlines.description: New Mexico tied a school and Mountain West Conference record for rushing touchdowns with eight Saturday in a season-opening 66-0 win over Mississippi Valley State.
headlines.shortLinkText: New Mexico beats Mississippi Valley State 66-0

events.name: Alabama A&M Bulldogs at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Gunner Kiel threw for a pair of touchdowns before taking the second half off with a big lead, and Cincinnati pulled away to a 52-10 victory over Alabama A&M in its return to campus.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cincinnati beats Alabama A&M 52-10 in return to campus

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles

headlines.description: Dak Prescott threw two touchdown passes and Brandon Holloway returned a kickoff 100 yards for another score to lead Mississippi State past Southern Mississippi 34-16 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mississippi State beats Southern Mississippi 34-16
